              <table id="EditorialReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Book Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">The heart of Zen practice and writing are the same, teaches Peter Matthiessen &#150; to freshen the mind and see things in a new way. On Zen and the Writing Life, Matthiessen chronicles his own 25 years of growth as both a writer and a meditator. Can meditation be used to broaden and clarify the writer&#146;s vision? How do you cultivate a "beginner&#146;s mind"? Here is an extraordinary writer&#146;s personal account of these never-ending tasks &#150; and essential listening for all writers interested in the spiritual life.</span>
              
</td></tr></table>
              <table id="CustomerReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Customer reviews:</DIV>
                
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Zen and the Writing Life</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
